                   "message":  "MENUBAR-FILE-SUBSTRATE: host File menu bar + MenuCommandHandoff FIFO (Dispatch A)\n\nFrontier step 3, Dispatch A of 2 (host-side substrate; Dispatch B wires the\neditor-shell drain + one-way routing). Begins making the shipped\nOpen/Save/Save-As authoring loop DISCOVERABLE via a File menu instead of\nkeyboard-only. editor-egui-host only; 0 Cargo.toml; no editor-shell changes.\n\n- crates/editor-egui-host/src/handoff.rs: new MenuCommandHandoff — a host-\u003eshell\n  FIFO command queue (bounded VecDeque\u003cCommand\u003e under one Mutex; push + drain\n  take the same lock; cap 64, drop-newest + warn on overflow). Deliberately a\n  different shape from the latest-only Handoff\u003cT\u003e aliases\n  (InspectorHandoff/SaveStatusHandoff): menu clicks are EVENTS that must not\n  overwrite one another. 2 inline tests (FIFO order + empties; bounded\n  drop-newest).\n- crates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs: EguiHost owns Arc\u003cMenuCommandHandoff\u003e\n  (constructed like the other handoffs), a menu_command_handoff() accessor, and a\n  re-export. EguiHost::render draws a TOP egui menu bar (File: Open / Save / Save\n  As New Project) before the bottom status bar; activating an item enqueues the\n  matching existing editor-ui::menus::Command onto the FIFO. file_menu_items() is\n  the single source of truth (shared by the bar + a test). 2 inline tests.\n\nIMPORTANT (scope): Dispatch A only makes the File menu VISIBLE and ENQUEUES\nCommands. There is NO functional menu effect yet — nothing drains the queue\nuntil the editor-shell drain + one-way routing lands in Dispatch B.\n\nAuthority / dependency guardrails: reuses the existing editor-ui::menus::Command\n(NO new command enum). \"Save As New Project...\" is LABELLED so but enqueues the\nexisting Command::SaveAs; Dispatch B routes Command::SaveAs -\u003e\nEditorShell::handle_save_as_new_project_request. MenuRegistry::resolve deferred.\nNo new dep edge (editor-egui-host already deps editor-ui).\n\nNew menu code uses the current egui APIs (Panel::top / MenuBar::new().ui /\nui.close), adding zero deprecation warnings; the adjacent bottom status panel\nkeeps its pre-existing egui::TopBottomPanel deprecation (present on main;\nmigrating it is out of this dispatch\u0027s scope).\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
